reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've had these cords for a little over a month amd I gotta tell ya not only do the my samsung galaxy S 23 super fast. They can take a beating. I have two cats and when I'm not charging my phone, the cats play with the cord. (I don't recommend this or at least unplug it first) the drag it, bite it, claw at it, play tug of war with it. It still charges my phone just as well as it did the day I got it. SUPERB!! I highly recommend these cords. You will not be disappointed!! Plus the price is a steal. You get way more than what you pay for. I guarantee it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Solid performance until phone hits the ground
reviews.reviewText: This is a great product. Never failed to charge and charged fast. Braid is tough. Only issue is I figured it could take a beating when you accidentally trip over the cord and phone comes crashing down onto wood floor, charge port first. The plug on the end of the cable bent enough to break some sort of connection inside because it stopped charging my phone. I put a different cable to the phone to double check and phone charged. It is my fault for the drop but figured this unit could handle it.

reviews.reviewTitle: Exceptional customer service, the product lived up to my expectations.
reviews.reviewText: I first got a cable and added a review with a 3/5 rating since it was difficult to connect with my devices. That same day the customer service contacted me to find out why I wasn’t entirely satisfied. By explaining the problem the supplier wanted to send me a second product that I received within 2 days. The cable works very well it is robust and of good quality. So I reviewed my evaluation to reflect their proactive customer service and product quality. A real pleasure to do business with them it was very satisfying.

I bought two of these now. It is very durable and you don't have to worry about the end closest to the port bending or coming undone like APPLE cords do! If they have an even longer one of these, I will order also. Worth every penny and more considering how much money I have spent replacing apple products. If you have kids, that pull on the cords, this is the best one to order.

This cable seems like it can take a lot of movement and I'm not worried at all that it will break or shred.The second time I plugged my phone in I got the "accessory may not be supported" message, but I haven't seen it since.Last night for the first time my phone got extremely hot while charging so I had to unplug it.It's extremely durable, though, and I will update my review if something goes wrong in the future.
